<% content_for :title, "Tips & Best Practices — Admin Manual" %>

<div class="flex gap-8 lg:gap-12">
  <aside class="hidden lg:block w-52 flex-shrink-0">
    <%= render "sidebar" %>
  </aside>

  <article class="min-w-0 flex-1">
    <%= render BreadcrumbComponent.new(items: [
      { label: "Admin Manual", path: admin_docs_path },
      { label: "Tips & Best Practices", path: nil }
    ]) %>

    <h1 class="mt-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-stone-900">Tips & Best Practices</h1>
    <p class="mt-2 text-stone-500">Recommendations for running your studio booking smoothly.</p>

    <div class="mt-8 space-y-6 text-stone-700">
      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5 text-sm space-y-2">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Set your schedule in advance</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          Use Bulk Create to generate an entire month of slots at once. You can always cancel
          individual slots later if the studio becomes unavailable.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5 text-sm space-y-2">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Publish your agreement before going live</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          Customers must accept the agreement before booking. The app won't let them proceed without
          a published version. Set this up before you create any public slots.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5 text-sm space-y-2">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Verify your hourly rate before the first booking</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          Once a booking is confirmed, the rate is locked in for that booking. Changing the rate
          later only affects future bookings — not existing ones.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5 text-sm space-y-2">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Set a cancellation window that matches your costs</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          If you incur prep costs the day before a session, set the window to 24 or 48 hours so
          you're protected. The window can always be adjusted in Settings; changes only affect
          future bookings.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5 text-sm space-y-2">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Let new customers sign up themselves</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          The public <strong>Sign Up</strong> link lets artists register and verify their own email
          without any admin work. Direct online inquiries to the Sign Up page and they'll be ready
          to book once verified.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5 text-sm space-y-2">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Create accounts for phone/email customers</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          If someone calls to book, create their account under Customers — it's automatically
          email-verified so they can book immediately. Then create the booking manually and
          optionally generate a Stripe Payment Link so they can pay online at their convenience.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5 text-sm space-y-2">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Check the dashboard regularly</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          The at-a-glance stats show open slots (available inventory) and reserved slots (confirmed
          revenue) for upcoming weeks — a quick health check without digging into Bookings.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-xl border border-stone-200 bg-white p-5 text-sm space-y-2">
        <p class="font-semibold text-stone-900">You can always refund</p>
        <p class="text-stone-600">
          If something goes wrong — a session falls through, equipment fails, the studio isn't
          available — cancel any confirmed booking from the admin panel. The customer is automatically
          refunded in full. No manual Stripe work required.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</div>
